<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FFBFE7548F75530FAE4FD8C" pageId="437" pageNumber="438" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418FFBFE7548F75530FAE4FD8C" blockId="437.[151,1436,503,636]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFBFE7548F75530FE9EFDC4" bold="true" box="[199,315,540,564]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFBFE7549745530FD81FDC4" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1922" box="[324,548,540,564]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Allodryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="437" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miripes">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFBFE7549745530FD81FDC4" box="[324,548,540,564]" italics="true" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">Allodryinus miripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FFBFE754A445530FD01FDC4" box="[628,676,540,564]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FFBFE754BAE5530FB64FDC4" authority="Kieffer, 1922" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1922" box="[926,1217,540,564]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Allodryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="437" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FFBFE754BAE5530FB84FDC4" box="[926,1057,540,564]" italics="true" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">Allodryinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08FFBFE754C195530FB64FDC4" author="Kieffer" box="[1065,1217,540,564]" firstAuthor="Kieffer" pageId="437" pageNumber="438" pagination="65 - 103" refId="ref361493" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1922) Philippine Serphidae (Proctotrupidae). The Philippine Journal of Science, 20, 65 - 103." type="journal article" year="1922">Kieffer, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(by monotypy and original designation). The 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FFBFE7549F0556CFE55FDA8" box="[448,496,576,600]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
has been deposited in the Baker's collection, that has been dispersed in many world collections. The 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FFBFE7549615548FE24FD8C" box="[337,385,612,636]" pageId="437" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
is apparently lost, because it was not possible to find it in the main world collections.
</paragraph>
